reviews.text: I like this mall. Before working here I wasn't a mall person but this mall has done a good job at keeping stores that are relevant to the people in the area. They still have mall events to bring people out and fun stuff for kids. They are opening a five and below soon which goes perfect with everything else. Metro is across the street, they have restaurants , a decent food court and department stores at every end. Plenty of beauty and barber shops also a lot of local business in the area of the mall.

When I first moved her, I really loved this mall but recently it seems they have been losing some of their stores. Now, there is not much for a selection related to the places I like to shop for clothes. Also, their stores close at weird time now. I went in on a Friday evening and several stores were closed at 830p, I understand it's winter. But dang! It's the weekend who is not at least open until 10p?!

This mall needs some serious investors to revamped it. It such a waist of time going there, the few little stores that are inside this building is not cutting it seriously. Here is a big spacious mall but lacks buyers attentions wants to spend their hard earn money. It was a waist of my time going here, this mall needs some top of the line stores inside their.

The center is getting up there in age and it shows. The parking lots are getting choppy with bumps and repairs from years gone by.  The tenant selection is just ok.  No super anchors. Just COSTCO and Target.  There is the typical mall fair inside that hold no interest for me.

Plenty of parking which may be a sign of things not so good.  Access from the main roadway is always pretty good.  At rush hour it can be a chore to make the lights getting in or out.

I was only disappointed they didn't have any wheelchairs.   It's not fair to disabled persons that because someone damage one chair, that you have none.   I don't have a car to transport my own chair so this was sad that I had to roll around the mall in a Cosco basket.
This is still my favorite mall, still full and vibrant.   So glad so many stores are still open.
Terrible place!! They don’t even understand what your saying even if you point. The portions are very little, instead of giving you a full scoop they only scoop half a spoon.

I took my son to the mall on Monday 4/01/22, it was lunch time and we were hungry. He wanted Popeyes , I opted for Subway, plz Subway. Why all of these commercials trying to convince us that you’ve improved. Plz stop! First the meat slices but they are so thin it’s ridiculous,I ordered a turkey and roast beef sub. The meat was barely there. If it weren’t for all of the veggies I heaped on I would’ve been eating a bread sandwich. I showed it to my son , he said” what did you order, I said look at my sub and you tell me”? He then told me  that he saw green peppers and lettuce. I ordered a veggie sub y’all  Lol what was laughable is that the you lady making my sub asked did I want it deluxe? So call deluxe iS, not a couple slivers of turkey and not one scrawny piece of roast beef, sliced to invisible! But 2 pieces of RB and this would mean more money for the already nearly there meat. This is the worst place to buy a sub period!!!! Not just in Wheaton but Subway has made and spent so much money on new ads and promotions when all they need to do is to put Some Meat on the Sub!!!!! Hey Subway, Where’s the Meat???????????!???!?!!??????!!!
They r  not pick phone call  i was calling last 25 munites

They didn’t want to give me how much toppings I wanted. I asked for a lot of lettuce and the lady gave me ten pieces of lettuce. I had to ask for everything I wanted twice because the lady wouldn’t give me how much I wanted. If I could give them zero stars, I would. I have never went to that bad of a subway. I will never eat at that Subway again.

Paid extra for a premium sub, I tried to get the garlic bread sub but the employee didn't know how to make it so the manager came over instead.  She took the bread I had wanted and made me get Italian bread instead without asking, only made half of the sub garlic bread even though it's supposed to be both and costs extra, then refused to put toppings on my sub because "you don't get toppings on meatball subs".  I emailed a complaint and the owner messaged back blaming a new girl even though it was his manager that messed it up and was just like, I hope you give us a second change.  Why should I when you didn't even take credit for anything and passed the blame?

I ordered a grilled chicken sandwich and this is how it looked. I went back to ask them because the meat was NOT cooked. They told me that’s how all their meat look. How could they be serving that chicken uncooked. Gross!!

This Subway never seems very busy and it's probably entirely because of parking challenges. I almost only walk anywhere so it doesn't bother me. The staff has always been very friendly and speak English fluently. The food ingredients are always fresh and quickly prepared. I get take out subs here a couple of times per week and have never had a bad experience.

I went to the store to order a sub for my daughter who has food allergies.  They ran out of the bread I usually order for her.  One of the workers went in the back to check the ingredients label of the other bread and came back to say the bread had no dairy.  I told her that I needed to see the label myself.  She said the box was too heavy to bring to me (it was 25 pounds).  I asked if she could take a picture of the label and she said no.  My issue is her attitude. If I was asking her to go above and beyond, then fine, but, respond with a poor attitude.  Other Subway stores have been helpful in either letting me see the bread box label myself or taking a picture of the label so I can read it myself when I have a question about ingredients.  Food allergies is serious and can be life threatening.  Food providers should work with customers with food allergies and not alienate them.
Pretty good service , Fresh food in my opinion. Will definitely come back .
Lots and lots of things are great about here!! The ladies that usually attend me are nice!!

Brought my in-laws here for birthday dinner. My in-laws are the most difficult people from an eating perspective- they are very picky, some are vegetarians, some are vegans, some can't handle spice, etc., etc., etc.
They were ALL happy with Ruan Thai! Plenty of different menu options and preparations. The servers were very good at helping people find the right dish and spice level.
I definitely recommend Ruan Thai. I can't wait to go there again (this time without the in-laws)!

Service was excellent and plenty of space to safely dine indoors. Starters and beverages came out quickly. Main courses soon followed. Overall the food was good. Definitely freshly cooked, but a bit lacking in flavor. The Pad Thai was very mild. Will be back to try a different dish.

It was a nice local Thai place that seems to be very popular. Very busy when I was there and having only one server was really a bad idea, unless someone called sick. The food came out fast and the service was fine with no issues. The food itself was ok, but way too high in sodium for me. I imagine all the dishes are done the same way as fish sauce is the base for most.

18. Sum Tom (Papaya Salad): The salad was really good and crunchy, very refreshing and fresh. Just the fish sauce in it was a bit more than needed, its better off on the side, as we can personally control the sodium content. The peanuts and tomatoes are a nice compliment and highly recommended if you enjoy interesting salads, just avoid the fish sauce and pour it on yourself.

16. Num Tok Tofu: I love the little bits of fried tofu with nice red onion and cilantro. But it was way too overloaded with fish sauce, causing extremely high sodium content. Please order it with sauce on the side, its the only way to save the dish and enjoy it. It is highly unnecessary to use that much fish sauce, its like drinking it. So if you order it, sauce on the side. Overall, crunchy tofu goodness.

25. Pad Khing (Stir Fry): It is good, but again was too much sodium in it. This dish destroyed me, gave me a headache, tummy ache, and my lips were dry after eating it. Its good, don't get me wrong, but way too high in sodium and they need to cut back on that black bean paste. This dish is extremely simple, you can to go an Asian market and simple buy Fried Tofu (3.99), Woodear Mushrooms (0.99), and Lee Kum Kee Black Bean Paste (3.49) and mix it together, thats pretty much it. It needs to be eaten over rich to drown out the salt.

40. Ganh Keow Whan (Green Curry): Their version of green curry is more watery than thick, they add peppers and veggies. The taste itself was not spicy at all and the taste and tangy. I got chicken and it was sliced nicely and was good, the jasmine rice was also nice and not hard, cooked more on the softer side. Its alright, but not something I would get again.

Thai Ice Tea: This was great, tasted like how you'ed think Thai Ice Tea would taste.

Not the best Thai place I've been too, but a nice place overall and good service.

One of the best Thai restaurants in MoCo. I love their pad thai and drunken noodle. Chicken satay was really good too. Staffs were friendly for most of the time, but they weren’t really attentive when the place got busier. They have a very limited shared parking spaces in front of the restaurant and you may likely have to do street parking. Highly recommended this place!

Around lunch time I googled food near me, clicked Thai food on the top of my screen. I looked at 3 Thai restaurants and chose this one because of the reviews. I should have eaten somewhere else. I dined in.The spring rolls were good, hot and crunchy. 5/5 would recommend I ordered for my entree the Pla Num Tok which is suppose to be crispy deep fried catfish with veggies. The fish was cold and I can tell it was deep fried at lease a couple days ago, refrigerated and microwaved. I’m super disappointed and would not recommend to anyone. This place also is not the cleanest when I was waiting for my food I can smell rag water and it smelled like they mop the kitchen and seating area with the same mop and mop water from the kitchen area.I’m very cautious and observant with cleanliness…..Ruan my meal.

Heard from a coworker that this is the "Local" food in Maryland, I didn't know Ledo Pizza was actually a popular chain around here, I thought it was generic, but they sure proved me wrong!

The Ledo Special 8-Inch Pizza: (14.99) Everything abput this pizza yelled out tasty. The bacon was crispy, meat was plentiful, veggies were balanced, this pizza was incredible. It isn't as salty as other pizzas and you can taste every topping on it. I am lovong the squares as it is less messy and easy to share. The crust was nice and soft, yet crispy.

Service was good and the prices are fine. The place is spacious and there is a lot pf room not to worry about social distancing. I recommend this place and Ill different be a regular from time to time.

I consider myself an amateur pizza connoisseur and after moving to MD and hearing so much about Ledo, I just had to try it. Not gonna lie, I’ve had better pizza at little squeezers but at least they’re cheap, Ledo cost 3 times that just for a 14” pizza & wings & mozz sticks. Pizza tasted like a giant lunchable, only highlight was the marinara sauce. Wings were definitely less than 1lb, felt like 6oz. The mozzarella sticks were breaded cheese sticks, pretty much room temp. Now, you’re probably thinking I ordered and came an hour later based on all this feedback, right? I WAS EARLY, so I guess if you’re looking for fast this place is has gotcha.

Family fun and friendly. Kinda reminds me this pizza place called the Pizza Inn I used to go to as a kid. I had the Buffalo chicken pizza with bell peppers. The ingredients were fresh, pizza was thin and crispy, and the sauce had just the right amount of kick. My mother and I sat in and I reviewed the menu while we were there. I'd recommend this place. I'm definitely looking forward to going back and trying out some of their other dishes. Thumbs "all the way up"
Had a really great salad. Food is consistently great here, as is the service.

Worst pizza I’ve ever had in my whole life. I have no idea what all the hype is all about. This taste like a bigger lunchable… and don’t get me started on the appetizers. I’d rather get mozzarella sticks and wings from the grocery store. Disappointing

Excellent, legit Chinese food! Love the dim sum, veggies, noodles - almost everything we have ordered has been really good. The people that run it are very nice. They have everything setup for as little contact as possible. Self-ordering at the table via a QR code, takeout collected from automated boxes, and a host/hostess on an iPad at the front.

Been customers 20-plus years... Have always loved the food. This time not so. Sesame chicken dry and hard with hardly any sesame seeds. Honey walnut shrimp, usually our favorite, tough and tasteless. Shrimp egg rolls bland. Ginger dumplings still fabulous. Questionable if we'll go back. If so, only because of so many other good experiences.

This was a great place for an early dinner with little kids. It's inside the mall and there is ample parking. We order using an app but the staff is very attentive with water and other stuff. They have both high chairs and boosters. The food was great and we felt very welcomed in the space as well.

In a nutshell, the food was great and the service is now horrible.
When it comes to taste, Hollywood East Cafe does not disappoint. We ordered the Honey Walnut Shrimp, Beef Lo Mein, Hunan Beef, and Crispy Beef and had the Roast Pork and Egg Drop soup as appetizers.  None of our dishes disappointed and the Honey Walnut Shrimp was a standout (as usual).

When it comes to service, we were very disappointed.  Hollywood East moved away from ordering from waitstaff to ordering from an app.  If you choose to order from a waitstaff it's very difficult to get their attention and actual service.  Our waitress sat the hostess stand to chat/vent with other staff. (I know they were venting because I could hear them and it had to do with not knowing who ordered certain dishes at tables because of the app). You need to wave them down, multiple times, to get service. You can order from the menus but they are takeout menus and the prices are outdated so you still need to go online to see current prices.  Essentially, they only have table runners and no wait staff.

I'll still keep going back, I have been a customer since they were on University/Veirs Mill, because the food always tastes so good. My expectations regarding service will need to be adjusted.

Tried here for our family’s Christmas Eve take-out meal.  What courses we received were delicious.  However, one family member came up empty as an order of Beef Bulgogi w/ rice was missing.  Shouldn’t have to open all sealed bags to double-check before leaving the restaurant.  Would appreciate a credit to our credit card [Order #207324939] if/when this oversight is confirmed by the restaurant.  Thank you for your efforts on a very busy holiday occasion.

UPDATE: We are entirely grateful to the owners for contacting us directly to explain the mistake and kindly adjusting the charge for the meal.  This type of response is why we prefer to patronize family-owned businesses, and particularly restaurants, for the obvious effort they continually provide to satisfy their customers.  We DO look forward to another visit as soon as possible, and thank you again, Hollywood East!

The best Peruvian chicken in the DC metro area.  This is the place that first started the rotisserie chicken 🍗.  All the others copied.  There are some others that are real good but this is the original.  Must try.

Hope you like it as much as my family and I do.

Visiting Maryland for work and some colleagues took me to El Pollo Rico for dinner. Never would have found or gone to this place on my own, so I’m grateful that they took me here. Definitely not the place to go if you’re prissy or even expect your restaurants not to look like a dive bar and be covered in a layer of grime and bathroom doors not locking and your fellow diners looking real sketch.

Considering that potatoes have been cultivated by Peruvians for 10,000 years I don’t know why I was surprised that they were fried to perfection. I love fries, but I hate most fries at restaurants, especially those wedge slices because they are never crispy enough. These fries where perfectly crispy outside and soft on the inside and were very airy. I’m amazed.

The chicken was perfectly cooked, seasoned and was very moist. The rice was good and the beans looked like perfection. Nice beautifully brown color to the beans and broth but would have benefited from some more salt.

Overall, I would recommend this place and wish there was one close to home for me.

It’s o.k. Standard Peruvian chicken joint turning out standard fare. Tried chicken, tamale and empanada. Price is on the lower side when compared to other chains. Chicken is precooked and comes out of a warmer. Chicken is juicy enough but can never tell how long it’s been in the warmer. Sides are good and serving size. Staff is polite and provide condiments as requested. This place is busy and parking in the plaza is available.

The chicken was delicious.  Well cooked and good flavor.  I had the white rice, red beans and plantains as sides.  They were good but as good as the chicken.  Definitely worth the trip if you like Peruvian chicken.

One of the better chicken places in the area. Very solid quality but not quite outstanding. Chickens have gotten pretty small and quality of meat is only fair. Fried are maybe 3 out of 5, ok but not with you going out of the way to order.

Store number:7906
Location: Wheaton, MD
Date/Time:December 25 at  11:47:21am

This was happen during christmas when we went to Wheaton and drop by some coffee at starbucks.
Please don't do that to your customer.  I ordered venti hot americano and they give this small cup and put on the venti cups whicks makes double cups on a venti size.

Absolutely best and Awesome Customer Service. On Friday I Accidently bought the wrong chocolate covered almonds and originally I was looking to buy there chocolate covered espresso beans 🤤 and after accidentally opening the almonds the manager approved me to be able to switch them out for the espresso beans free of charge. He didn't even hesitate. He was absolutely the Nicest shift leader/ Manager I have ever come across. This store is top notch also never have had a drink made wrong or anything if it has ever happened they have always fixed it immediately 👌☕

It's worth taken extra drive to this location next to Giant if you do not live in Wheaton. Nothing but positive experiences especially with the crew and guy who's either the shift leader or manager!!!. This happened on Friday 8/26/2022 @ 4:00pm I forgot his name so this was the day he was working and helped me with the exchange.

Our visit was great. It was a Saturday afternoon so there was no line. The store was nice and clean. The baristas were friendly and got our order correct. Coffee was fresh and hot. The young lady on the register made sure I got the best deal using my reward. Overall great experience.

All the staff provide great customer service. I always have great experiences at this store. Their services keep exceeding my expectations making me adjust my expectation up, and they keep meeting or exceeding!
Especially, many thanks to Richard who has done an amazing service that has exceeded my already high expectations.
super delicious and friendly 😀🥰 vegan hot drinks -yummie

It's been a while since I last had a meal here. Everything was good I was amazed at the amount of changes they have made to their menu. And very good changes 👏 👌  I had the Protein strawberry and banana pankekes with a Chicken Poblano Omelet with Black Coffee it was delicious, amazed by the taste of the pankekes that they didn't taste like protein (that dirt, bitterness taste)

Typical breakfast fare at IHOP
Breakfast pancakes, hot and fresh, price is right.
All servers seemed nice, however, my service was so SLOW!! I'm just one person.
Okay, it was busy, and I give her a break( and a tip) even though other tables came after me with families, and were served before me by a different servers😔

Waited 10 minutes to be greeted after walking in although there was someone standing at the register. It would have been fine if someone had just said “hi, we will be right with you” don’t make eye contact with me and then blatantly ignore me. Was finally seated at a gross table, waited another 10 minutes for someone to come take our drink order. We left without ordering and we went when it’s wasn’t busy.

The service was awful tonight. I always come to this place, not sure what happened tonight. Today the drinks took too long, the order was incompleted. I asked for appetizer and never got it (Server apologize for). We asked for dessert and the food was sitting on the counter for a while and nobody brought it to the table… so we decided do not take anymore…!!! Sometimes has to improve.

The service was not good. The place is in the middle of all the streets close to viers mill rd. The seating is cramped like they tried to put a restaurant in the middle of chaos which brings me to the service. I was sitting for 30 minutes before my order was placed and didn't get food until an hour later. I ordered French toast eggs and sausage. I was given French toast with eggs and bacon. When told the order was wrong. My plate was picked up and bacon scraped off replaced with sausage. There was a lack of empathy from the server about getting the order wrong as if I was an inconvenience. I know the place was busy but the least you could have done was reassure that the order was coming (I shouldn't have to ask you after 30 min) and refilled the glass with water...which you did NOT do. Very disappointed and won't go back unless no other options. Food good...not the service.

I am very sure Ill end up learning spanish through this place, as I will come here many times while am around.

This chicken is absolutely amazing, the seasoning makes KFC and Popeye utter nonsense, its in a league of its own. Of course, crispy lovers may not get the monster crispiness from here, but I would say it is a good level of crispy to strong seasoning, giving it a good balance.

The french fried and Yuca fries are good, no conplaint on that, the service is wonderful and fast. I was nervous because everyone was speaking Spanish (Of course they speak English too) during order pick ups, but I thought it was funny, when everyones number was being called in Spanish and then suddenly my order comes out in English.

All in all, absolutely amazing chicken!

Everything was very Beuno~
Thats correct right?

Back to back nights, asked for a plain chicken sandwich and given a sandwich full of pickles

This last time I asked for a sanwich “plain no pickles” and a side of nuggets and even asked “you sure you got the sandwich plain and side of nuggets” he looked at me and said yes… i got no side of nuggets and sandwich covered in pickles

I just don’t get it, I said it slowly and clearly thinking I talk to fast but to no avail smh
…..

—— UPDATED 8/6

I have been back multiple times… this location really struggles with a simple “No Pickles” like even this last time I can see the marks where the pickles have been sitting on the bun and can taste the pickles that you had on this sandwich….not to mention it took 20 min to make the sandwich

Its so simple make the chicken, put it on a bun and hand it to me… I am baffled that 12 straight orders have been messed up… so baffled
Amazing restaurant and the service really good! The store is always very good, The cashiers very friendly. The manager very professional, He’s doing a good Job

Family friendly place where You may either dine in, get deliveries via partner apps or take out. It’s a great place to go for tasty chicken! If you are hungry and do not want to wait to long; this is the place to go. Their chicken is moist and tasty; whether it is fried or grilled. I also enjoy there yucka, plantains and coleslaw sides. The valued meal are affordable for families. Staff is nice and friendly and it’s clean. So far, it’s one of the best place to get chicken in the Wheathon-Glenmont area.

OMG, a place better than Popeyes? How is that possible...
Clearly they cater to a different audience, had I not been hungry and been in the right place at the right time, I would have never eaten there, just for names sake, but damn, the best deep fried chicken I've ever had, no kidding.

The food is very authentic Cantonese. They have one of the best wonton beef noodle soup and kingdom pork chop in this part of town. The roast duck and roast pork are also up to par. Been there for carry out many times and finally ate there last night. Was not impressed by their salted fish chicken fried rice nor the eggplant salted fish casserole. But the clams in black bean sauce and beef chow foon  is also highly recommendable. The place and service is mediocre as expected of a Chinese place but it’s definitely not a hole in the wall. Could be a bit tight if it was filled but it’s mostly carry out. And I mean seriously busy carry out so that is a good sign!!!

The best Chinese/Hong Kong style restaurant in MD!!  Highly recommend their Wonton Noodle Soup, Seafood Pan Fried Noodles, Baby Clams in Black Bean Sauce, Beef Brisket and Deep-Fried Shell-On Shrimps with Spicy Salt.  Majority of their dishes are delicious, you can’t go wrong.

Their Roast Pork and Roast Duck are especially the best in the DMV—I have yet to find anywhere that compares!

4.5 for legit Cantonese/Hong Kong style Beef chow fun and Wonton Noodle soup ($13). The noodle is al dented and the soup was piping hot with full flavor. My mom always asks to eat here when she visits from Florida, claiming it's the best bowl of wonton noodle she has in the US. There's even hard to find, ginger scallion Duck blood stir fry. Weve been eating here for over a decade and almost forgot about them due to COVID. Glad we came back today. Don't let the dated decor deter you from the food. There's also hanging whole roast duck and the usual Cantonese fare. You can tell the Sifu(chef) is a seasoned chef as the stirfry served quickly and fresh/hot. Give this low key family restaurant a try.

Back at one of the old favorite and it’s still good.  (It must been several years since last visit.). The Shrimp Wontan Noodle Soup has been the reason for us to come here.  The price went up but the noodle portion got bigger.   The roast duck was good too.   I think they used to offer combo platter with duck, pork and chicken.

The service was ok and as long as I can remember the service wasn’t strong point here.

I had the Cantonese style egg noodle soup.  It was topped with the most tender roast pork I've ever had.   One is given the option to add wontons stuffed with pork and shrimp,. So I did.  That's a no brainer.  The egg noodles were plentiful and cooked to chewy perfection.  Last but not least the simple, savory flavor of the beef broth cooked made me wish I had room for more!  This broth also had a mild sweetness that I've never had in a soup before.  Now all this goodness is packed in just one bowl.  Their menu is filled with so many authentic style Cantonese cuisine.  So please try something other than General TSO's, even though it's awesome.  I can't wait to come back!!!!!

Me and my American husband ordered Spicy Floating Market Noodles Soup and Chicken Curry Puffs. Everything was delicious as real Thai style. we give them high score for these dishes. I really love the spicy broth. We'll definitely come back when we have a chance.
Boat noodle soup for the win. Recommend the papaya salad with preserved crab

Ordered through Uber eats. We get there to pick upthe food and this place is closed! Waste of driving to come here. Who closes a restaurant on a Saturday??! Never ordering from here again since they don’t update hours and don’t want to get surprised like this again.
The food was flavorful.   My chicken was a bit dry.  People were very friendly.   There were only a few customers there on a Friday night.   May have been due to construction nearby.

Strongly recommend shrimp pot!! Bean noodles of sesame oil flavor. Avoid american styled thai food like fried tilapia.

It's hard to find parking near here, we parked on the back of the building.

I visited the restaurant for the first time on a recommendation from someone who has eaten there for years and described the food as authentic.The food was exquisite, very flavorful! I ordered the black pepper short ribs, scallops in black bean sauce and Szechuan spicy dumplings (very spicy, indeed!). I had enough food to eat leftovers twice.

Old school & authentic. My old man's go to place to get duck and bbq pork. Who cares about ambiance when you can get large portions of delicious food. Make sure to check out the small pink stand up menus for great noodle soups, rice dishes, and congee

Possibly the best roast pork in the area but other foods are in a steep decline. The duck had a sour taste, the crispy roast pork was full of large bones, and the service was rather indifferent. Despite other restaurants being full on a Friday night, this place was a ghost town. This will be our last time here. Go to Full Key instead

Love the food here. Glad they remodeled years ago. You can't go wrong with their fish, lo mein, fried shrimp, aboloni mushrooms , Chinese watercrest, sweet and sour fried pork. Service is great and food comes out fresh
There for a new year banquet. Delicious fried lobster and sautéed flounder. But the dining room is old and needs renovation.

The food was SO delicious. I purposely kept enough for dinner later that day. I asked advice on getting something spicy and the server offered to have the spicy add in put on the side. Good thing I did because 1/2 of it was more than enough for me 🤣 Will definitely visit again when in the area.
Found this Vietnamese place by random when we were visiting the Wheaton Costco and got hungry! Love the food and amazing taste! Everything we had was very good
I enjoy the Pho, Vietnamese iced Coffee & pork bun. Staff are friendly and fast. I order carry out often. All the food is authentic and tasty.

Everything we have tried so far is awesome!! Prices are also cheaper compared to those in eden (with its great quality). It’s just i dont know why they don’t have delivery partners to order delivery
> Cơm tấm is a must try. Their com tam is the best in dmv. i’d say it tastes so much like places i love in vietnam
> Mi la cay is also a must try!
Our go-to Vietnamese place in the area. The servers are really nice. The ambiance is great. I always order Maryland Chicken and it never disappoints.

Used to go here as we were growing up. It was great! For the past 15 years or so, however, it sucks. Always wet and greasy, mushy chicken. I end up going a couple times a year because I have hopes that it will be like out used to be, and the taste when done right is much better than Popeyes. Every single time, whether dine in, take out, or delivery, it is the same. To the owners: please quality check your chicken. It should be better. I’ll keep trying every once in a while out of nostalgia, and hope that you guys return to what I remember. I think you would have more business if you improve.

KFC is really young their game. The best chicken sandwich of any day food chain. The fried chicken is crispy and juicy too! Currently open!! Clean new design and yummy fried chicken. If only there were more coupons available...

This rude spanish girl at the drive thru taking order without even greeting, got my order wrong. This place is dirty, disgusting and expensive. Never coming back again. Just go to other branches its better.

This is the size of the wing they gave me in the combo. The vanilla wafer is almost the size of it. I'd have gone back, but I did pickup. By the time I got it out of the box,  I was already home which is way to far away. Never see me again.

This location was renovated not long ago. The ugly tile & the unmovable chairs on a single pole locked into the floor are gone. Looks better. The menu is updated and easier to read. The restroom was clean. As for the food quality: the usual. IMPORTANT NOTE: Never go thru the drive-thru at this location. Always slow. Walk in and check the line. If too long, find another place as the service is slow.
There's a woman that works here , I should get her name, she works the front register most mornings. ..she is an absolute delight. She's always smiling and friendly and greets people well.

I ordered the chipotle chicken egg with no wrap , the order came as a wrap and I asked to modify, all that panera did was to dump everything from the wrap to the bowl while I was watching and Handed back to me :(
Awful customer service

I love Panera Bread's food. It's pretty drafty (cold in the winter) because of where it sits in the mall. Good place to go for a bite to eat. Love their soups and they have friendly service. We even met Matthew Lesko there (or a look-a-like ... not sure)! 😄

I'm not giving 5 stars for 2 reasons: first the cashiers were talking and even when we have eye contact didn't approach to the register to take my order I have to ask who was going to do it so they can stop the conversation, also noticed that the portions of food were smaller than other Panera Bread Restaurants. Everything else was good, food served fast and delicious, place was clean.

Like the new items added to the fall menu like the toppings you can add to the mac and cheese. Also the salads were good. One thing they have to work at this location is their attention to details. They forget to add certain ingredients on the salads very often. You have to carefully check your order every time.

Wonderful place with nice patrons.
Went there to watch a soccer game.
Was told by regular patrons to try their food & it was delicious.
I got the prime rib Queen cut which comes with mashed potatoes and mushrooms & it was delicious and a big portion.
Meat was fresh and tasty.
The bartender Elisia was super nice and interactive with everyone.
Paid meter parking across the street.
Definitely recommend this place if you’re in the area.

In the spirit of supporting neighborhood businesses, I ventured over to Limerick Pub. Why did I do that to myself? I ordered the crab dip (no crab and covered in uncooked bread crumbs accompanied with cold  chips).  For my entree, I requested a medium-well burger with a fried egg and bacon. Once cut, I was greeted by a dry, well done patty. The mediocre crab dip I boxed to go thinking I could fix it up at home but the burger, the burger was sent back to be re-done. Shortly after, the older red-headed bartender returned to inform me that the cook was unable to make a medium well burger. Apparently, he’s a one-trick chef and that trick is over cooked beef. The bartender then argued with me about the fact that there was no difference between “well done” and “medium-well”. Needless to say, I returned the food and just opted to dine on beer. I’d say I’m disappointed but honestly, annoyed is best suited.

If you want beer, come to the pub. If you want decent bar food, choose unplugged or one of the other options.

We trekked to Wheaton especially for prime rib steak night since we had never eaten steak there before. Maybe that was a mistake since this is an Irish bar and grill, but nonetheless we decided to order the 16 oz. Prime rib steak. Customer service was off from the start. No one came outside to take our order so we went inside to the bar where we also were ignored for over 5 minutes but then told the waiter would take our food order outside. Luckily, we were at least given a beer since we then had a 20 minute wait. During that time, we and the folks at a table next to ours took turns going back inside to see if a waiter would come. While we waited, we noticed another table of 4 get up and leave, complaining that they had waited over 15 minutes after ordering. As they left, the waiter ran behind them and convinced them to return. Only after serving that table did the waiter come to our table to take our order. That incident alone would be enough to send even the most patient customer on their way. Perhaps that would have been the best option for us as well. Instead, we stayed and awaited our steak with anticipation; we were pretty hungry by then.  When the steak arrived, it had the biggest slab of fat I had ever seen. I would say the fat slab was almost the same size as the non-fat part...maybe 60/40. We ate the steak which was cooked appropriately, trimming off the 3+ inches of fat and leaving it on the plate. Trying to get the waiter's attention to pay is a similar story....Once we got his attention, I pointed out to the fat and said that with so much fat, we only really only got a 12 oz steak, so that is all we should pay for. The waiter noted that he would have to speak to the bartender about that. Next thing we know, the bartender barrelled to our table and proceeded to "educate" me about cuts of steak.  When I saw where that was going (no where), we handed him the credit card and said to just forget the $5.00 difference. He took the card still muttering as he went back inside. To my surprise, it was the bartender and not the waiter who then returned with the credit card. This time he raised his voice louder saying he took the $5.00 off and he then began pointing his hand in my face saying that next time I order a steak, it shouldn't be prime rib since it's always that fatty. I have really never seen such poor customer service all around. From being ignored to being insulted and almost assaulted, I am still reeling from this experience one week later.
Beautiful pours of Guinness. Delicious desserts that seemed homemade. They called last call and let people linger while they got ready for the next. Good atmosphere, good people

Happy hour specials are really good at lower cost, both food & drink. All of their food is great. I really like the fried mushrooms & the shepherds pie potato skins apps. But they are all good. I Always enjoy this pub.

I placed a order of pupusas (pork & cheese) what I received was 2 pupusas with a lot of cheese and no pork.. I went back to tell them I asked for pork & cheese not only cheese..I received my pupusas thinking they had fix the problem I received my pupusas without cheese and only pork.  Very dry & no flavor.. I was not expecting this I usually order pupusas here all the time very disappointing!

Delicious, authentic Latin American food. I’m Nicaraguan so it passes the test! Breakfast is top notch too. The bread is stellar. I also recommend the pupusas. Been coming here for years when I’m home!
I lived in Corpus Christi as a kid and this place reminded me of the panaderías we used to visit. Recommended!
The food tastes like it's been decomposed.... no. Disappointed with this people just want to collect the money.
Small place but many different types of latin bread/ pan dulce 🍞 🥖 🥐 .

reviews.author_name: Unique & Interesting People of the World
reviews.text: The food is not good.  The restaurant is not clean.  I saw a roach crawling on one of the chairs at the end of my dinner.  The service is terrible.  One of the workers by the name of Maria was very rude to me when an asked for extra sauce.  I will never go back here.

I honestly don't understand how this place is scored so high.  I went once and will never go again.  Maybe as a bar and hang out? As a restaurant however, no way.  The food is not good.  There are so many restaurants around Wheaton with amazing Spanish food.  This place is not it.
Bad service all night, got my order wrong the whole stay. Corona with no lime was a red flag. Waitress's completely ignore you. Save your money and avoid at all costs!!!
Food was decent and staff was super serious and had attitude. Didn't feel welcome to this restaurant/bar. Definitely won't be coming back.

Was a little disappointed by the complimentary salsa that came at the beginning of the meal, but everything that came after that was legit. Some great flavors. A great representation of Central American cooking. Some nice cocktails too.

The ambience is laid back and unpresumptuous.
